# Conventional commits (semantic-release)

This repo uses [semantic-release](https://semantic-release.gitbook.io/) on `main`. **Every commit message you write or suggest must follow the Conventional Commits spec** so releases and changelogs are generated correctly.

## Format

```
<type>(<optional scope>): <short imperative summary>

<optional body>

<optional footer(s)>
```

- **Subject line**: lowercase type, imperative mood, no trailing period, ~72 chars max
- **Scope** (optional): area of change, e.g. `circle`, `bracket`, `tabs`, `ci`, `deps`
- **Body**: only when the why/how is not obvious from the subject

## Types (semantic-release)

| Type | Release | Use for |
|------|---------|---------|
| `feat` | minor | New user-facing capability |
| `fix` | patch | Bug fix |
| `perf` | patch | Performance improvement |
| `revert` | patch | Reverts a prior commit |
| `docs` | none | README, comments, AGENTS only |
| `style` | none | Formatting, whitespace, no logic change |
| `refactor` | none | Code change without fix or feature |
| `test` | none | Tests only |
| `build` | none | Build tool or dependency changes |
| `ci` | none | GitHub Actions, release config |
| `chore` | none | Maintenance, scripts, misc |

**Breaking change** → major version: add `!` after type/scope (`feat!:`) or a footer line `BREAKING CHANGE: <description>`.

## Examples

```
feat(circle): show national badges and flags on elimination chart
fix(tabs): group bracket and circle under knockout parent tab
ci: add semantic-release and tag-based GitHub Pages deploy
chore(deps): add semantic-release plugins
fix(bracket): prevent mobile card overlap on small screens
feat!: remove legacy groups tab from bracket view
```

## Do not

- Use vague subjects: `update`, `changes`, `wip`, `fix stuff`
- Use past tense: ~~`added feature`~~ → `add feature`
- Capitalize the type: ~~`Feat:`~~ → `feat:`
- Mention semantic-release/changelog in normal commits (release commits are created by CI with `chore(release): … [skip ci]`)

When generating a commit message in Cursor (Source Control or agent), infer `type` and `scope` from the diff and match this format exactly.
